<HEAD>Slaughter Named AP Newsfeatures Director</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Slaughter </PERSON>, a general executive on the headquarters staff of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, has been named director of <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Newsfeatures </ORGANIZATION>. Slaughter succeeds <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Perkes </PERSON>, who is retiring after 32 years with the news cooperative. <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Newsfeatures </ORGANIZATION> develops and markets syndicated features and books, including `` The Associated Press Stylebook'' and `` The Word,'' a guide to newswriting. <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> announced the appointment on Monday. <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> said that in addition to his Newsfeatures duties, Slaughter will assist in development of <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s strategic plan under Vice President <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Brien </PERSON>, who is director of strategic planning and <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> treasurer. Slaughter, 40, was transferred to the AP headquarters staff in August after four years as <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s chief of bureau in <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION>. He went to <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION> after five years as chief of bureau in <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J </LOCATION>. He joined the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Topeka </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kan. </LOCATION>, in 1973 and worked in <LOCATION> Sioux </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Falls </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.D. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION> before being named correspondent in <LOCATION> Cheyenne </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Wyo. </LOCATION>, in 1976. He was correspondent in <LOCATION> Tallahassee </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, and assistant chief of bureau in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> before being named <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION> bureau chief in 1980. Slaughter is a native of <LOCATION> Salina </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kan. </LOCATION>, and a graduate of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kansas </ORGANIZATION>. He also holds a master's degree in business administration.
