<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leftist rebels fired at least 16 shells from homemade mortars at the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> Monday but most exploded in nearby streets, killing a gas station attendant and wounding 15 other people. President <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON> accused <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>'s Sandinistas of either supplying the weapons or parts and technical skill for their construction to the rebels. The <ORGANIZATION> Farabundo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> FMLN </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-, an umbrella organization of guerrilla groups, had announced in February it was suspending the use of homemade mortars in populated areas because their inaccuracy caused civilian casualties. <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON> told a news conference the attack was `` an attempt by the <ORGANIZATION> FMLN </ORGANIZATION> to give the impression it is strong. `` But they -LRB- the rebels -RRB- have only the capacity to stage terrorist actions.'' Col. <PERSON> Rene </PERSON> <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Ponce </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Joint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chiefs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Staff </ORGANIZATION> said eight shells struck the grounds of the <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Social </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> adjacent to the ministry compound but no one was wounded there. Authorities said the other shells exploded in adjoining civilian neighborhoods. <LOCATION> Ponce </LOCATION> reported 30 unfired shells were found on two trucks from which the other shells had been launched. The trucks were in a shopping mall about 300 yards from the military compound. The shells on one truck were covered with garlands of