<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions, Nov. 10-12, and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>The Artists: Upstaging at the Met</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY16 of Oct. 30</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 In the Metropolitan Opera's new production of `` Rigoletto,'' the title role is sung by <PERSON> Leo </PERSON> <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Duke </ORGANIZATION> is <PERSON> Luciano </PERSON> <PERSON> Pavarotti </PERSON> and soprano <PERSON> June </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> makes a much anticipated Met debut as <PERSON> Gilda </PERSON>. But <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>'s not worried about being upstaged. `` When you have a great cast and a great conductor, we perform much better,'' he says. The Italian baritone was one of the top stars of the Met last season, acclaimed as <PERSON> Figaro </PERSON> in `` The Barber of <LOCATION> Seville </LOCATION>'' and in `` Rigoletto,'' `` Madama Butterfly'' and `` The Elixir of Love.'' He gave the Met four months which, he says with a smile, he probably wo n't do again. <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON> is in demand in opera houses all over the world. He started this season singing in <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Hamburg </LOCATION>. He'll be at the Met for only `` Rigoletto,'' the first seven performances of nine during November and two in February. In January he'll sing the role in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>. During <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>'s fall engagement here, he'll sing the 1,000 th performance of his career and his 100th Rigoletto Five recordings on <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Records </ORGANIZATION> will come out this season: `` The Barber of <LOCATION> Seville </LOCATION>,'' `` Rigoletto,'' `` <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> <PERSON> Boccanegra </PERSON>,'' `` Aida'' and a solo record of Italian songs. `` A Masked Ball,'' the last recording conducted by <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Karajan </PERSON>, was released by <PERSON> Deutsche </PERSON> <PERSON> Grammaphon </PERSON> in August while <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON> was singing in that opera at the <LOCATION> Salzburg </LOCATION> Festival. <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>, interviewed in his manager's office, said his early career progressed in an unusual way. His opera debut was in 1967 in the title role of `` The Barber of <LOCATION> Seville </LOCATION>'' in <LOCATION> Spoleto </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>. `` After three years, I am stopping the career. I was then in the chorus at <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Scala </LOCATION> five years. Why I do n't know. Do n't ask me why. Because of life. Many things. Things were n't going so well. Thinking about the voice technique,'' he said. `` When I did my audition for the chorus, the chorus maestro said, ` You're sure you come to the chorus?' I said, ` I'm sure. I need the money for eating.' I never lost the habit of eating. This is a big problem. `` I started again to study. I find in Milano a teacher; he was 85 at the time. I was with this old man until he died at 90 years old. In 1973, I made another debut, in <LOCATION> Lonigo </LOCATION>, a very small city. At the same time I was in the chorus at <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Scala </LOCATION>. In 1975 I take another important decision, with my wife and family. I left the chorus.'' He dates his career from that time. `` I'm glad and I'm very lucky. To stop the career and try again is not so easy.'' Another good thing happened during <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>'s stint in the chorus. `` I find my wife. She is a soloist, soprano. She listened to me sing a song, a very romantic song. She fell in love. I was already in love, to sing the song. We married in 1972.'' <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON> sang his first Rigoletto with his wife, <PERSON> Adriana </PERSON>, who was six months' pregnant, in <LOCATION> Lonigo </LOCATION>. `` She also sang in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> and Covent Garden. She is retired now. `` My daughter, <PERSON> Cinzia </PERSON>, <PERSON> Cynthia </PERSON> in English, is 16. She tries to be a soprano but it's too early to know about this.'' <PERSON> Nucci </PERSON>'s big break came in 1978, sin