<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For proof that the tube is booming for older actors, look no further than this year's Emmy Awards. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Mulligan </PERSON>, 56, won best actor in a comedy series, and <PERSON> Carroll </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON>, 65, won in a drama series. Other nominees included <PERSON> Colleen </PERSON> <PERSON> Dewhurst </PERSON>, 63; <PERSON> Doris </PERSON> <PERSON> Roberts </PERSON>, 59; <PERSON> Eileen </PERSON> <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> and <PERSON> Diahann </PERSON> <PERSON> Carroll </PERSON>, both 54; all four `` Golden Girls''; <PERSON> Angela </PERSON> <PERSON> Lansbury </PERSON>, 64; and <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Dysart </PERSON>, 60ish. `` I think that's indicative of the effect older actors are having on television,'' said <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Golden </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> GTG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION>'s vice president for talent. `` We're finding that these days it seems to be hip to be older,'' <PERSON> Golden </PERSON> said. `` The pilot movie for our series ` Baywatch,' which features mostly young actors, had a lifeguard in his 60s. He died in the movie but tested so well we're going to add an older lifeguard to the series. `` We're developing a comedy series that focuses on a man in his 70s.'' <PERSON> Deborah </PERSON> <PERSON> Barylski </PERSON>, an independent talent agent who has cast many comedy series, is placing more older performers than ever before. `` The scripts I'm getting are paying a lot more attention to that kind of character. `` When I cast ` Frank's Place' we used so many elderly people that I really had to do a lot of digging to find new actors in that age range.'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Golden Girls,'' starring <PERSON> Bea </PERSON> <PERSON> Arthur </PERSON>, 63; <PERSON> Betty </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, 67; <PERSON> Estelle </PERSON> <PERSON> Getty </PERSON>, 66; and <PERSON> Rue </PERSON> <PERSON> McClanahan