<TEXT>
 Three major Wall Street firms capitulated to an investor outcry, abandoning or curtailing a computerized trading strategy widely blamed for turmoil in the stock market. In addition, an insurance company that manages more than $ 8.6 billion in assets stopped doing business Friday with brokerages that conduct program trading and the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> said it would contact members about possible reforms. <ORGANIZATION> Morgan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stanley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, two of the biggest users of program trading, said they would stop using a form of the strategy known as index arbitrage to trade for their own accounts. <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> ended use of all forms of the strategy.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Americans' personal income, dealt a blow by Hurricane Hugo, rose a lackluster 0.3 percent in September as consumer spending posted its weakest advance in a year, the government said. The <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said Friday that personal income in September rose $ 12.8 billion at a seasonally adjusted annual rate to $ 4.47 trillion, the smallest increase in four months. Spending increased 0.2 percent, the most anemic gain in 12 months, to an annual rate of $ 3.53 trillion.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The federal budget deficit totaled $ 152.1 billion in fiscal 1989, marking the third year of essentially unchanged fiscal red ink, the government said. For the first time, interest on the $ 2.8 trillion national debt exceeded Social Security spending, pushing the interest category into second place, behind military expenditures. The budget gap for the year ending Sept. 30 marked a $ 3.1 billion, or 2 percent, improvement over the $ 155.2 billion deficit in 1988, the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Budget </ORGANIZATION> said Friday.
