<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The manufacturer of an inhaler for asthmatics is recalling the medication after just one month on the market because of reports of coughing, choking and gagging after use, the <ORGANIZATION> Food </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drug </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> said. The drug is a new formula of a commonly prescribed metered dose inhaler _ alupent. The <ORGANIZATION> FDA </ORGANIZATION> said Friday the medication is being removed from the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> market because there has been a sharp increase in reports of adverse reactions with the reformulation.
