<HEAD>Unocal Third-Quarter Earnings Fall 19 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Unocal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday its third-quarter profits fell 19 percent due to escalating costs to produce oil and gas and lower refining and marketing results. For the three-month third period, the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles-based </LOCATION> oil, gas and coal company earned $ 79 million, or 67 cents a share, down from $ 97 million, or 84 cents a share, in the comparable 1988 quarter. Revenue rose 8 percent to $ 2.8 billion from $ 2.6 billion. <ORGANIZATION> Unocal </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stegemeier </PERSON> said the quarter's negative results were partially offset by higher crude oil prices and improved domestic natural gas production A $ 6 million after-tax gain from the sale of land in <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, and a $ 14 million reduction in deferred income taxes resulting from changes in the company's state taxes also contributed. For the first nine months, <ORGANIZATION> Unocal </ORGANIZATION>'s profits fell 16 percent to $ 286 million, or $ 2.44 per share, from $ 339 million, or $ 2.91 a share. Revenue rose 14 percent, to $ 8.5 billion from $ 7.5 billion.
