<HEAD>Japanese Company Buying Controlling Stake in Rockefeller Group</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to CLARIFY relationship between Rockefeller
Group and Rockefeller Center, and to include comment from the trust committee
that family members will not benefit directly from the sale. Picks up 5th
graf pvs, `Our agreement ...'. SUBS 8th graf, `Four years ...,' to clarify.
ADDS 1 graf on Mitsubishi's holdings.</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY81</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Estate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, a major Japanese real estate concern, announced Monday it will buy 51 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the private real estate and entertainment company controlled by descendants of <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr </PERSON>. The $ 846 million cash purchase will give <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> majority control of <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Music </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Cushman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Wakefield </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> real estate firm and <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, the landmark, 22-acre <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> development built by <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON>. Last month, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> confirmed media reports that it was seeking an outside investor to buy part of the company. The reports indicated that some <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON> family members, who control the company through trusts, wanted more income from their investments. Most of the family members' inheritance is tied up in real estate and other corporate holdings. But the independent trust committee that manages the family's trusts said the money from the sale to <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> would be reinvested in other company operations <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bowen </PERSON>, chairman of the trust committee, said one objective of the sale was to diversify the company's holdings, which are concentrated in real estate. `` Our agreement with <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Estate </ORGANIZATION> preserves the abiding commitment to <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, which my father made more than 50 years ago, and which present generations of the family continue to feel,'' <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>'s chairman, said in a statement <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Voell </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>'s president and chief executive, said the purchase of the 627,000 shares in the company by <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> `` ensures the company's ability to continue to invest in Rockefeller Center to enhance its stature as the most modern and prestigious commercial complex.'' He said <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>'s board, its advisers and the trust committee considered other options, such as a recapitalization funded by debt, before they decided on the sale. Four years ago, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> refinanced <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> by taking out a $ 1.3 bilion mortgage on some of the rentable space, then selling shares in that mortgage to the public through a real estate investment trust. The company also manages <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>. The Rockefeller family fortune was built by <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON>, founder of <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and was estimated at $ 900 million by 1911. His son, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, created five trusts for his children in 1934. Those trusts are the principal owners of <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, with descendants of <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rockefeller </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> the main beneficiaries. The Rockefeller Center complex includes the General Electric Building, formerly known as the RCA building, Radio City Music Hall and the Time-Life building. <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>'s other businesses include: <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telecommunications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Music </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Cushman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <LOCATION> Wakefield </LOCATION>, in which the company holds an 80 percent stake. <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Estate </ORGANIZATION> is one of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s largest real estate companies. Its other major <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> investments include partnerships that built a $ 500 million office building at <OR